Aim:
To write a program using Pandas to create and display a DataFrame and use Matplotlib to plot the data.

Algorithm:
s1 - Start
s2 - Import the pandas library as pd and matplotlib.pyplot as plt.
s3 - Initialize two lists: Points containing the scores and Teams containing the MotoGP team names.
s4 - Create a DataFrame using these two lists with columns "Points" and "Teams".
s5 - Display the DataFrame using the print() function.
s6 - Create a new plotting figure using plt.figure().
s7 - Plot the graph using plt.plot() with Teams on the x-axis and Points on the y-axis.
s8 - Set the title of the graph as "MotoGP Team Points".
s9 - Label the x-axis as "Teams" and the y-axis as "Points".
s10 - Display the graph using plt.show().
s11 - Stop
